00:19:52,317 --> 00:19:53,318
- Yeah.
- And...

260
00:19:53,985 --> 00:19:54,986
whenever...

261
00:19:56,112 --> 00:19:57,864
I'm the one who gets the mail.

262
00:19:59,574 --> 00:20:03,286
<i>And whenever I see a postcard
in the pile,</i>

263
00:20:03,328 --> 00:20:06,164
<i>I try to put it picture side up.</i>

264
00:20:06,206 --> 00:20:11,294
<i>That way, I have something
to turn over. To discover.</i>

265
00:20:12,003 --> 00:20:14,172
Something I'm hoping for.

266
00:20:17,509 --> 00:20:20,720
It's funny 'cause...
we're all following you,

267
00:20:20,762 --> 00:20:23,765
reading articles,
doing all that stuff and...

268
00:20:23,807 --> 00:20:26,893
You know, you can't not know that...

269
00:20:27,686 --> 00:20:29,771
we feel, I mean...

270
00:20:32,357 --> 00:20:35,026
We all feel a sort of...

271
00:20:36,611 --> 00:20:37,612
admiration.

272
00:20:38,488 --> 00:20:39,489
For you.

273
00:20:40,073 --> 00:20:41,449
Sounds silly, but...

274
00:20:42,617 --> 00:20:43,618
It's a gift.

275
00:20:43,868 --> 00:20:45,370
You have a gift.

276
00:20:48,456 --> 00:20:49,457
You're laughing?

277
00:20:50,166 --> 00:20:51,209
Yeah, I...

278
00:20:51,251 --> 00:20:54,879
Why? It's a gift, that's it.

279
00:20:54,921 --> 00:20:56,339
It's not funny.

280
00:20:56,840 --> 00:20:58,383
I'm complimenting you.

281
00:20:58,883 --> 00:20:59,884
You got a gift.

282
00:21:00,468 --> 00:21:01,636
You're lucky.

283
00:21:02,721 --> 00:21:06,641
Yeah 'cause...
You don't really use it with us.

284
00:21:07,726 --> 00:21:09,227
It's for others.

285
00:21:09,728 --> 00:21:11,730
Or maybe for no one.

286
00:21:13,773 --> 00:21:15,734
I don't know you.

287
00:21:16,234 --> 00:21:20,238
I'm just saying that.
I'm not judging.

288
00:21:20,822 --> 00:21:23,742
Those are facts.
I'm thinking out loud.

289
00:21:25,410 --> 00:21:28,747
Fucking kills me. I'm so itchy.

290
00:21:28,788 --> 00:21:29,831
What?

291
00:21:29,873 --> 00:21:31,499
I dunno, the makeup.

292
00:21:35,295 --> 00:21:37,714
I never use it, so it itches.

293
00:21:37,756 --> 00:21:41,301
I just wanted... I dunno.
Know what I mean?

294
00:21:41,343 --> 00:21:44,512
And Mom's makeup is shit.

295
00:21:44,554 --> 00:21:47,474
It's red and gross,
so I bought this stuff.

296
00:21:51,853 --> 00:21:53,730
Don't you wanna sit down?

297
00:21:55,273 --> 00:21:56,858
It's cozy.

298
00:21:57,150 --> 00:21:58,777
I'm good.

299
00:22:18,338 --> 00:22:19,464
Those are all mine.

300
00:22:20,423 --> 00:22:23,802
<i>We just call them
your "elliptic bits."</i>

301
00:22:24,302 --> 00:22:26,513
<i>Maybe "elliptic" is wrong.</i>

302
00:22:26,846 --> 00:22:27,847
<i>No.</i>

303
00:22:28,390 --> 00:22:30,141
<i>I mean...</i>

304
00:22:30,183 --> 00:22:31,559
<i>I get it.</i>

305
00:22:31,601 --> 00:22:33,603
<i>We each have our collection.</i>

306
00:22:34,312 --> 00:22:35,563
<i>Antoine.</i>

307
00:22:36,481 --> 00:22:37,982
<i>Mom, obviously.</i>

308
00:22:38,024 --> 00:22:39,234
<i>And she's right.</i>

309
00:22:39,275 --> 00:22:43,029
<i>You've never forgotten the...
our birthdays.</i>

310
00:22:44,322 --> 00:22:46,616
<i>The important days of our lives.</i>

311
00:22:46,908 --> 00:22:49,953
<i>Always a postcard, always something.</i>

312
00:22:50,787 --> 00:22:52,956
Anyway, I dunno.

313
00:22:53,248 --> 00:22:56,418
I've stopped complaining 'cause...

314
00:22:56,960 --> 00:23:01,172
She lectures us when we dare
say you're... not around.

315
00:23:02,590 --> 00:23:05,760
"He does what he has to do.
He always has."

316
00:23:06,302 --> 00:23:07,554
She says that?

317
00:23:07,595 --> 00:23:10,557
Of course. I didn't make it up.

318
00:23:10,598 --> 00:23:14,519
But don't worry, I'm an adult, I...

319
00:23:15,020 --> 00:23:16,521
No problem.

320
00:23:16,563 --> 00:23:17,731
No problemo.

321
00:23:18,106 --> 00:23:19,607
No!

322
00:23:20,734 --> 00:23:22,610
No problemo.

323
00:23:22,652 --> 00:23:24,696
Dunno why I said that.

324
00:23:25,321 --> 00:23:26,865
I hate that.

325
00:23:27,365 --> 00:23:28,575
It's not me.

326
00:23:28,616 --> 00:23:31,578
I hate that expression,
it's ridiculous.

327
00:23:31,828 --> 00:23:33,413
So what is "you"?

328
00:23:33,455 --> 00:23:36,916
It's weird how you always
send postcards,

329
00:23:36,958 --> 00:23:39,002
as if you're on vacation,

330
00:23:39,044 --> 00:23:41,588
and mailmen can see what you write.

331
00:23:41,921 --> 00:23:43,340
I dunno.

332
00:23:43,840 --> 00:23:48,386
Do you let everyone see
the important things you write?

333
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:52,015
Well, what you write isn't...

334
00:23:53,475 --> 00:23:54,893
Okay, this is just...

335
00:23:55,143 --> 00:23:56,978
Pathetic. I'm pathetic.

336
00:23:58,271 --> 00:24:00,065
Everyone says so.

337
00:24:00,648 --> 00:24:02,150
Sorry.

338
00:24:03,568 --> 00:24:05,278
I didn't mean to...

339
00:24:06,196 --> 00:24:08,365
I'm sorry, Suzanne.

340
00:24:10,909 --> 00:24:12,369
No, it's me.

341
00:24:13,745 --> 00:24:15,497
I'm sorry.

342
00:24:21,586 --> 00:24:24,631
Friggin' heat wave
is driving us crazy.

343
00:24:25,048 --> 00:24:26,800
And here it's worse.

344
00:24:27,133 --> 00:24:29,052
Everything's worse here.

345
00:24:29,761 --> 00:24:33,056
I wanted to leave but, I dunno...

346
00:24:33,807 --> 00:24:35,100
I'm good here.

347
00:24:35,141 --> 00:24:37,060
Got the basement,

348
00:24:37,102 --> 00:24:39,479
my room, the storage.

349
00:24:40,230 --> 00:24:42,107
That's the room behind you.

350
00:24:42,899 --> 00:24:46,569
Shit from the old house.
Yours, mostly.

351
00:24:46,611 --> 00:24:49,948
Mom's gonna ask
if you want any of it.

352
00:24:50,824 --> 00:24:52,117
Bet you don't.

353
00:25:25,942 --> 00:25:27,360
Louis?

354
00:25:27,986 --> 00:25:29,446
Are you listening?

355
00:25:29,487 --> 00:25:32,032
Yeah, stuff you bought yourself.

356
00:25:33,158 --> 00:25:34,784
Did you buy the car?

357
00:25:36,119 --> 00:25:37,829
Antoine's old one.

358
00:25:39,289 --> 00:25:40,915
<i>Mom bought it.</i>

359
00:25:41,332 --> 00:25:43,043
<i>Mom doesn't drive.</i>

360
00:25:43,376 --> 00:25:47,130
<i>Mm-hmm, so guess
who's her slave driver?</i>

361
00:25:47,172 --> 00:25:51,176
<i>But I can drive downtown,
see the girls.</i>

362
00:25:52,802 --> 00:25:54,679
<i>And I drive Mom for errands.</i>

363
00:25:55,138 --> 00:25:57,098
<i>We don't depend on anyone.</i>

364
00:25:58,475 --> 00:26:00,185
<i>We bother no one.</i>

365
00:26:01,061 --> 00:26:04,606
<i>And I like those little moments
with Mom.</i>

366
00:26:07,192 --> 00:26:08,526
<i>She's fun.</i>

367
00:26:09,319 --> 00:26:11,196
<i>She's nuts, though.</i>

368
00:26:13,490 --> 00:26:14,657
Anyway...

369
00:26:17,243 --> 00:26:18,828
No.

370
00:26:18,870 --> 00:26:22,874
I knew you'd say no.
Smoking isn't very you.

371
00:26:24,334 --> 00:26:26,044
Are you completely high?

372
00:26:26,461 --> 00:26:27,921
No.

373
00:26:28,380 --> 00:26:30,090
I hardly feel it anymore.

374
00:26:31,966 --> 00:26:34,552
In fact, it might do me good.

375
00:26:35,053 --> 00:26:37,722
- I don't usually smoke, but...
- So?

376
00:26:37,764 --> 00:26:38,765
Why you here?

377
00:26:39,933 --> 00:26:42,227
Got someone to introduce?

378
00:26:42,644 --> 00:26:44,396
Are you pregnant?

379
00:26:46,272 --> 00:26:48,483
For you. For, uh...

380
00:26:50,694 --> 00:26:52,404
I don't know.

381
00:26:53,446 --> 00:26:55,949
I'd love to see our old house.

382
00:26:56,324 --> 00:26:57,617
Why?

383
00:26:57,659 --> 00:27:00,704
Why do you wanna go back
to that ugly place?

384
00:27:02,497 --> 00:27:04,874
I don't know. Out of nostalgia.

385
00:27:05,291 --> 00:27:07,252
Is it for a play?

386
00:27:07,293 --> 00:27:08,878
No.

387
00:27:11,131 --> 00:27:12,632
No.

388
00:27:13,008 --> 00:27:16,052
<i>Suzanne! Louis! Are you coming?</i>

389
00:27:16,094 --> 00:27:17,345
Stop screaming!

390
00:27:17,762 --> 00:27:19,806
<i>Well, get the hell up!</i>

391
00:27:21,349 --> 00:27:23,852
Check out the storage room
if you want.

392
00:27:24,269 --> 00:27:26,312
And your old stuff.

393
00:27:26,938 --> 00:27:28,773
Out of nostalgia.

394
00:27:35,155 --> 00:27:37,198
Reminds me of our Sundays!

395
00:27:37,240 --> 00:27:39,159
- Ugh! Please!
- What?

396
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:42,412
She knows about Sundays.
Be honest, say it!

397
00:27:42,454 --> 00:27:44,039
Let her talk, Antoine.

398
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:47,584
He's embarrassed.
His Majesty longed for adventure!

399
00:27:47,625 --> 00:27:50,462
That's why he went
to China after college.

400
00:27:51,629 --> 00:27:53,840
- You went to China?
- So?

401
00:27:54,424 --> 00:27:58,094
So, I was working,
my husband was working...

402
00:27:58,136 --> 00:28:00,180
Bottom line, we both worked.

403
00:28:00,221 --> 00:28:01,723
There you are, sweetie!

404
00:28:01,765 --> 00:28:04,100
It's story time. Lucky you!

405
00:28:04,517 --> 00:28:06,519
- Our Sundays?
- Ha! See?

406
00:28:06,811 --> 00:28:08,438
Even Louis, Mom!

407
00:28:08,480 --> 00:28:10,023
Let us be, Antoine.

408
00:28:10,065 --> 00:28:11,441
Louis, red?

409
00:28:11,483 --> 00:28:13,610
Louis's always white, dear.

410
00:28:13,651 --> 00:28:16,946
- White, please.
- Only our family did that!

411
00:28:16,988 --> 00:28:20,825
It was a family thing.
Our thing! Mine, too.

412
00:28:20,867 --> 00:28:22,369
It was a tradition.

413
00:28:22,410 --> 00:28:23,995
Do you need a hand?

414
00:28:24,037 --> 00:28:26,831
Nah, calms me, just getting ahead.

415
00:28:26,873 --> 00:28:28,792
I wanna tell my story!

416
00:28:28,833 --> 00:28:31,127
Go on, let's get it over with.

417
00:28:31,169 --> 00:28:33,546
Sunday was our day off.

418
00:28:33,797 --> 00:28:38,510
So we went out for a ride.
Systematically.

419
00:28:38,551 --> 00:28:40,303
Systematically!

420
00:28:40,345 --> 00:28:42,847
It was like... a ritual.

421
00:28:43,640 --> 00:28:45,100
What are you doing?

422
00:28:45,141 --> 00:28:46,810
Nothing. I'm listening.

423
00:28:46,851 --> 00:28:48,478
Stay, Antoine.

424
00:28:49,020 --> 00:28:53,024
Forget him. Listen to me.
He loves to upset me.

425
00:28:53,441 --> 00:28:57,529
So, we'd go on an outing.
And we'd take the car.

426
00:28:58,113 --> 00:29:00,615
Their dad always owned a car.

427
00:29:00,657 --> 00:29:04,244
Here, back then, owning a car...

428
00:29:04,661 --> 00:29:06,287
But he worked.

429
00:29:06,329 --> 00:29:07,539
It was his car.

430
00:29:07,580 --> 00:29:11,501
It was old, ugly and noisy,
but it was his.

431
00:29:11,918 --> 00:29:13,878
Sunday mornings,
he washed it.

432
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:16,589
Washed the hell out of it.

433
00:29:16,631 --> 00:29:19,926
And after lunch...
Hop! Off we went.

434
00:29:20,343 --> 00:29:22,137
Every Sunday! A tradition.

435
00:29:22,178 --> 00:29:24,431
No vacations, but every Sunday,

436
00:29:24,472 --> 00:29:25,932
come shine or rain...

437
00:29:25,974 --> 00:29:29,144
No! "Come rain or shine,
hell or high water."

438
00:29:29,185 --> 00:29:32,731
Rain or shine, hell or high water.
You're right!

439
00:29:33,606 --> 00:29:37,986
He had expressions like that
for every situation in life.

440
00:29:38,028 --> 00:29:39,654
- He did?
- Yes.

441
00:29:39,696 --> 00:29:43,116
"He did?" You shitting me?
You know all this!

442
00:29:43,158 --> 00:29:45,201
Why tell stories we already know?

443
00:29:45,243 --> 00:29:47,829
We do that in life,
stop being so stiff!

444
00:29:47,871 --> 00:29:51,499
We recall and relive
the things we love.

445
00:29:51,541 --> 00:29:55,211
I know she knows,
but I enjoy telling her again.

446
00:29:55,462 --> 00:29:57,797
That's why we remember! For me!

447
00:29:57,839 --> 00:29:59,090
Happy?

448
00:29:59,132 --> 00:30:01,801
If you hate it so much,
cover your ears,

449
00:30:01,843 --> 00:30:05,430
beat it and stop cheesing us off!

450
00:30:05,889 --> 00:30:07,057
Cheese off?

451
00:30:07,098 --> 00:30:10,977
Damn right! Means piss off!
Your brother's specialty.

452
00:30:12,312 --> 00:30:16,733
So, the first Sunday in May,
or after March 8th...

453
00:30:16,775 --> 00:30:18,568
My birthday, of course.

454
00:30:18,610 --> 00:30:23,406
Or if the 8th was a Sunday
we hit the jackpot!

455
00:30:24,074 --> 00:30:28,828
That was the real deal.
We'd drive an hour or two.

456
00:30:28,870 --> 00:30:33,208
Fields, forests, castles,
vineyards, sometimes.

457
00:30:33,667 --> 00:30:38,129
We'd stroll, eat on the grass,
take a nap...

458
00:30:38,380 --> 00:30:40,090
On the plaid blanket.

459
00:30:40,131 --> 00:30:43,051
Tuna salad, rice,
mayo, deviled eggs.

460
00:30:43,093 --> 00:30:45,553
Antoine still loves
that salad, right?

461
00:30:45,804 --> 00:30:47,806
Always says "Make your salad!"

462
00:30:49,182 --> 00:30:50,308
He's sulking.

463
00:30:51,226 --> 00:30:52,769
And then, uh...

464
00:30:53,603 --> 00:30:57,774
Night came, and we'd be weary
from the drive,

465
00:30:58,066 --> 00:31:01,945
and we'd walk in and say,
"Home, sweet home!"

466
00:31:03,571 --> 00:31:06,783
Proof that all those
fancy trips to the beach,

467
00:31:06,825 --> 00:31:09,953
airports, planes,
sassy attendants...

468
00:31:11,579 --> 00:31:13,039
Anyway...

469
00:31:15,458 --> 00:31:18,962
Then, well,
the boys got older and...

470
00:31:21,965 --> 00:31:24,134
Well, Suzanne arrived!

471
00:31:24,801 --> 00:31:28,680
The boys had their bikes,
went their separate ways.

472
00:31:28,722 --> 00:31:31,558
And we stopped
the Sunday outings, `cause,

473
00:31:31,599 --> 00:31:34,811
with only Suzanne,
it wasn't worth it.

474
00:31:36,396 --> 00:31:38,273
Our fault, again.

475
00:31:38,773 --> 00:31:40,358
Or mine, Antoine.

476
00:31:41,526 --> 00:31:43,319
Heavens!

477
00:31:43,737 --> 00:31:46,281
Suzanne, I don't believe it!

478
00:31:46,322 --> 00:31:48,700
Yeah, drop it, Mom!

479
00:31:48,742 --> 00:31:49,868
But...

480
00:31:49,909 --> 00:31:51,828
I'm gonna kill myself!

481
00:31:51,870 --> 00:31:55,331
That's our day?
Dumb memories and shit music?

482
00:31:55,373 --> 00:31:58,168
- Fucking hell!
- It's our song, Suzanne.

483
00:31:58,209 --> 00:32:01,504
- Drop it, Mom! Jeez!
- Our aerobics song!

484
00:32:01,546 --> 00:32:04,507
- We're taking off.
- Suzanne, come!

485
00:32:04,549 --> 00:32:06,134
You outta your mind?

486
00:32:06,176 --> 00:32:08,970
You do aerobics?

487
00:32:09,012 --> 00:32:11,139
Piss your pants!

488
00:32:11,181 --> 00:32:13,350
I adore this song.
Suzanne, come!

489
00:32:13,391 --> 00:32:15,143
I'm obsessed,
it's a real find!

490
00:32:15,185 --> 00:32:17,062
Everybody found it, Mom!

491
00:32:17,103 --> 00:32:20,357
- You just live in a parallel world.
- I googled it.

492
00:32:20,398 --> 00:32:23,318
Translation said it's about
Picasso being in love,

493
00:32:23,360 --> 00:32:27,072
or Picasso...
Anyway, it wasn't clear.

494
00:32:27,113 --> 00:32:28,948
Come on, now!

495
00:32:28,990 --> 00:32:30,241
No!

496
00:32:30,283 --> 00:32:33,370
Make it a perfect day,
impress your brother!

497
00:32:34,371 --> 00:32:35,997
Don't embarrass her!

498
00:32:36,414 --> 00:32:39,042
Suzanne, please!

499
00:32:39,084 --> 00:32:42,087
Suzanne, come on!

500
00:32:42,128 --> 00:32:43,838
Come show them!

501
00:32:44,714 --> 00:32:47,217
All your moves are wrong,
it's a disaster.

502
00:32:47,258 --> 00:32:48,593
Well then come.

503
00:32:48,635 --> 00:32:52,055
Show your poor old mom how to do it.

504
00:32:52,097 --> 00:32:54,015
Alright, one, two...

505
00:32:58,269 --> 00:33:00,605
God, Mom, you're terrible!

506
00:33:00,647 --> 00:33:03,358
Looks like you're having a stroke.

507
00:33:06,903 --> 00:33:09,739
Mom, focus instead of
hitting on the teacher!

508
00:33:09,781 --> 00:33:12,200
In his dreams, maybe!

509
00:35:11,319 --> 00:35:13,029
Yes?

510
00:35:14,322 --> 00:35:17,325
Where are you,
why does it say unknown?

511
00:35:19,786 --> 00:35:21,371
Oh, right.

512
00:35:25,875 --> 00:35:27,585
Not yet, no.

513
00:35:33,133 --> 00:35:35,927
I've been here for an hour,
I can't just...

514
00:35:36,594 --> 00:35:38,972
shove it in their face.

515
00:35:41,891 --> 00:35:45,228
It was tough with my sister.

516
00:35:47,522 --> 00:35:49,024
I don't know her.

517
00:35:51,443 --> 00:35:53,069
She's so pretty.

518
00:35:54,571 --> 00:35:57,657
And so much older. It's nuts.
The others too.

519
00:35:57,699 --> 00:36:00,827
And I am too, of course.
I don't see myself.

520
00:36:07,459 --> 00:36:10,170
I don't know, after lunch maybe.

521
00:36:10,754 --> 00:36:13,631
Over coffee and dessert.
I don't know.

