How time has modified or...

794
00:56:25,093 --> 00:56:26,928
wrecked them.

795
00:56:28,138 --> 00:56:31,725
It's not even for sale.
You can't visit it.

796
00:56:31,766 --> 00:56:34,978
I drove by last week, and...

797
00:56:35,395 --> 00:56:37,313
it's completely abandoned.

798
00:56:38,565 --> 00:56:42,485
You wanna go back to that shithole,

799
00:56:43,111 --> 00:56:47,824
to see how time has wrecked,
modified it.

800
00:56:48,074 --> 00:56:51,494
Is that the most la-di-da
shit plan you got?

801
00:56:51,536 --> 00:56:52,662
Antoine.

802
00:56:52,704 --> 00:56:56,624
I meant no offense but...

803
00:56:56,666 --> 00:56:58,126
Of course not.

804
00:56:58,168 --> 00:57:01,421
It took us 20 years
to get outta there,

805
00:57:01,463 --> 00:57:05,842
and you want to go see
if the wind has wafted

806
00:57:05,884 --> 00:57:09,637
the autumn leaves
onto the rusted roof?

807
00:57:09,679 --> 00:57:12,140
What the fuck? Who cares?

808
00:57:12,182 --> 00:57:15,935
Leave him alone, he just
wants to go for a ride.

809
00:57:15,977 --> 00:57:17,395
I mean...

810
00:57:18,438 --> 00:57:21,358
I'll come with you,
Louis, if you want.

811
00:57:21,399 --> 00:57:22,984
Doesn't matter.

812
00:57:23,026 --> 00:57:25,695
- It was a bad idea.
- No shit!

813
00:57:25,737 --> 00:57:29,282
I'll beat off in Auschwitz,
jizz out a poem!

814
00:57:29,324 --> 00:57:31,659
Antoine! Bad taste!

815
00:57:31,701 --> 00:57:33,078
Alrighty, Louis!

816
00:57:34,162 --> 00:57:37,665
Give us some gossip!

817
00:57:37,707 --> 00:57:39,292
Let's dish!

818
00:57:40,377 --> 00:57:41,961
I don't know any.

819
00:57:42,003 --> 00:57:44,130
Well, make it up!

820
00:57:44,631 --> 00:57:46,966
You know, showbiz gossip!

821
00:57:47,008 --> 00:57:50,762
Who screwed who, who was screwed.

822
00:57:51,096 --> 00:57:52,722
Your fingers stink.
You smoked?

823
00:57:52,764 --> 00:57:53,807
Wine, Louis?

824
00:57:53,848 --> 00:57:55,642
- No thanks.
- You smoked.

825
00:57:58,019 --> 00:58:00,605
I don't know any gossip.
I don't go out.

826
00:58:04,025 --> 00:58:07,237
Coffee, Mr. Louis?
I was going to make a pot.

827
00:58:07,278 --> 00:58:10,782
What century d'you
Misses and Misters live in?

828
00:58:10,824 --> 00:58:13,410
What's it to you, dumbass?

829
00:58:13,451 --> 00:58:16,079
For fuck's sake,
am I talking to you?

830
00:58:16,121 --> 00:58:18,665
Stop fucking picking on me,

831
00:58:18,998 --> 00:58:20,834
telling me to shut up.

832
00:58:21,167 --> 00:58:23,086
Telling me I'm stupid.

833
00:58:23,128 --> 00:58:25,046
Stay the fuck outta this.

834
00:58:25,088 --> 00:58:27,549
Kids, no. Not this.

835
00:58:27,590 --> 00:58:30,051
Do you hear that?
What's that tone?

836
00:58:30,468 --> 00:58:32,345
It's well deserved.

837
00:58:36,850 --> 00:58:40,228
- You never talk to me like that.
- I'm starting!

838
00:58:40,270 --> 00:58:43,606
That's my tone when
you fucking annoy me!

839
00:58:48,695 --> 00:58:50,655
Never mind, I got it.

840
00:58:50,947 --> 00:58:53,742
That's too cute!
You're a cutie pie...

841
00:58:53,992 --> 00:58:55,368
Aren't you?

842
00:58:55,410 --> 00:59:00,081
Wanna look cool in front of
your bro? 'Cause he's here?

843
00:59:00,540 --> 00:59:02,792
This is for you, Louis.

844
00:59:03,168 --> 00:59:06,379
Is it working?
Are you impressed, Loulou?

845
00:59:06,421 --> 00:59:08,465
Rou-lou-cou-lou-lou!

846
00:59:10,008 --> 00:59:11,926
Loulou! Yoohoo!

847
00:59:13,094 --> 00:59:17,223
This is a load of bullshit.
It's bullshit. Mom!

848
00:59:17,265 --> 00:59:19,142
Suzanne, the neighbors!

849
00:59:21,019 --> 00:59:23,146
You make no sense!

850
00:59:23,188 --> 00:59:25,440
This isn't about Louis!

851
00:59:25,482 --> 00:59:29,486
Why d'you always humiliate me?
Humiliate everyone!

852
00:59:29,861 --> 00:59:32,113
This day fucking sucks!

853
00:59:33,156 --> 00:59:34,949
Suzanne, come back!

854
00:59:34,991 --> 00:59:37,786
Gosh, and you just let her go!

855
00:59:38,203 --> 00:59:39,454
She'll be back.

856
00:59:41,081 --> 00:59:43,375
Lord. Such a shame.

857
00:59:49,047 --> 00:59:51,299
Catherine, I'd fancy
a cup of coffee.

858
00:59:51,341 --> 00:59:54,844
"Catherine, I'd fancy
a cup of coffee."

859
00:59:54,886 --> 00:59:55,929
Antoine.

860
00:59:55,970 --> 00:59:59,474
What? Antoine, Antoine!
Yes, Antoine! What?

861
00:59:59,516 --> 01:00:01,685
That's my goddamn name, yeah!

862
01:00:01,726 --> 01:00:04,688
All day long!
Fucking pain in the ass!

863
01:00:13,113 --> 01:00:14,114
Fine.

864
01:00:14,864 --> 01:00:17,117
I'll work on my timing!

865
01:00:17,158 --> 01:00:21,037
I was about to say
it's lovely being together.

866
01:00:24,332 --> 01:00:26,334
Later, maybe.

867
01:00:37,470 --> 01:00:39,139
Excuse me, Catherine.

868
01:00:39,514 --> 01:00:40,932
No worries.

869
01:01:00,035 --> 01:01:03,705
We're not complete boors.
What's wrong with you?

870
01:01:04,039 --> 01:01:06,624
Why are you being so hostile?

871
01:04:33,665 --> 01:04:34,833
Louis?

872
01:04:37,168 --> 01:04:39,129
- Sorry.
- Sorry!

873
01:04:40,588 --> 01:04:43,717
I'm... Martine's asking for you.

874
01:04:43,758 --> 01:04:47,846
Dessert will be ready in 30 or 40.
Would that be alright?

875
01:04:48,221 --> 01:04:49,848
I'll be right up.

876
01:04:49,889 --> 01:04:51,391
Alright.

877
01:04:52,058 --> 01:04:53,309
Sorry.

878
01:05:15,915 --> 01:05:17,542
How much time?

879
01:05:35,435 --> 01:05:37,437
How much time what?

880
01:05:41,858 --> 01:05:44,652
How much time...

881
01:05:48,948 --> 01:05:50,742
Will you, um...

882
01:05:51,659 --> 01:05:55,663
Antoine's alone upstairs and...

883
01:05:56,998 --> 01:05:59,042
You could talk to him.

884
01:06:05,632 --> 01:06:07,425
I'm coming.

885
01:06:43,044 --> 01:06:44,587
So, um...

886
01:06:45,588 --> 01:06:47,215
I need a smoke.

887
01:06:48,174 --> 01:06:49,843
Gotta buy smokes.

888
01:06:49,884 --> 01:06:52,387
Well, you can... Never mind.

889
01:06:53,096 --> 01:06:54,389
Yeah, I know.

890
01:06:54,889 --> 01:06:57,851
Don't rat out Mom,
I hate her fancy cigs.

891
01:06:57,892 --> 01:07:00,228
I never smoke but when I smoke...

892
01:07:00,645 --> 01:07:01,980
I smoke.

893
01:07:03,898 --> 01:07:06,609
- And you need to smoke, right now.
- Mm-hmm.

894
01:07:09,654 --> 01:07:13,450
You coming? If you want,
in the car, we could...

895
01:07:14,117 --> 01:07:15,118
What?

896
01:07:15,618 --> 01:07:19,456
- Talk?
- No. I mean... I guess, yeah.

897
01:07:21,624 --> 01:07:22,834
Yeah.

898
01:07:23,960 --> 01:07:26,421
- I need some fresh air.
- Well, then.

899
01:07:27,422 --> 01:07:28,715
Done.

900
01:07:32,052 --> 01:07:35,180
I actually flew in early.
Traveled overnight.

901
01:07:35,722 --> 01:07:39,059
I wanted to see the sunrise
at the airport,

902
01:07:39,517 --> 01:07:41,478
eat at the small café.

903
01:07:42,854 --> 01:07:47,233
Thought I'd come
for breakfast, but...

904
01:07:48,526 --> 01:07:51,363
I waited for the proper moment.

905
01:07:52,530 --> 01:07:55,533
You're telling me this... because?

906
01:07:56,201 --> 01:07:58,536
What should I say?
Anything specific?

907
01:07:58,578 --> 01:08:02,665
No. I don't know,
just wanted you to know.

908
01:08:03,041 --> 01:08:04,584
It's not important.

909
01:08:05,377 --> 01:08:08,880
I told you 'cause it's true.
I wanted to tell you.

910
01:08:10,298 --> 01:08:11,716
Listen...

911
01:08:11,758 --> 01:08:13,385
Don't start, okay?

912
01:08:20,975 --> 01:08:22,477
Don't start what?

913
01:08:22,519 --> 01:08:24,437
This, Louis. This.

914
01:08:24,479 --> 01:08:28,191
Don't smother me
with airport stories...

915
01:08:28,233 --> 01:08:32,070
Should've come earlier, later...
I drown in that crap.

916
01:08:32,112 --> 01:08:33,321
Not in the mood.

917
01:08:38,284 --> 01:08:42,288
So you traveled last night?
How was it?

918
01:08:45,250 --> 01:08:46,918
Come on!

919
01:08:47,168 --> 01:08:50,839
It went fine, I guess.
It's a short trip.

920
01:08:51,256 --> 01:08:54,718
You guys think I live on
another planet.

921
01:08:54,759 --> 01:08:57,721
Coming here's not
the end of the world.

922
01:08:58,179 --> 01:09:00,849
But if you don't want to talk,
it's fine.

923
01:09:00,890 --> 01:09:02,308
Please!

924
01:09:02,642 --> 01:09:04,769
I'm listening, alright?

925
01:09:05,353 --> 01:09:07,772
Go on, tell me.

926
01:09:08,189 --> 01:09:10,400
I want you to. Come on!

927
01:09:10,442 --> 01:09:13,319
I want to know.
The airport, the café.

928
01:09:13,653 --> 01:09:15,989
The heat's driving us nuts, okay?

929
01:09:16,031 --> 01:09:18,324
No, you're right.
It's irrelevant.

930
01:09:20,160 --> 01:09:23,038
I just thought that...
I don't know.

931
01:09:23,830 --> 01:09:28,168
You'd be happy... or glad.
To know that, this morning

932
01:09:28,209 --> 01:09:31,796
I was at the airport café.
Remember the café?

933
01:09:32,255 --> 01:09:33,631
Waiting.

934
01:09:35,300 --> 01:09:38,345
I couldn't show up at dawn
and scare them.

935
01:09:39,262 --> 01:09:43,683
I can see Suzanne
on the porch, with a shotgun.

936
01:09:44,809 --> 01:09:46,978
She's such a pothead.

937
01:09:47,437 --> 01:09:51,316
She'd grab it upside down,
blow a hole in her head!

938
01:09:53,526 --> 01:09:54,986
You done?

939
01:09:55,820 --> 01:09:57,989
I was waiting,
thus I said to myself...

940
01:09:58,031 --> 01:09:59,115
Thus?

941
01:09:59,157 --> 01:10:00,283
Thus!

942
01:10:00,658 --> 01:10:01,826
Thus!

943
01:10:02,327 --> 01:10:04,704
- Thus...
- I was waiting, and...

944
01:10:04,996 --> 01:10:08,667
I thought I'd tell you about this.

945
01:10:08,708 --> 01:10:11,086
About being there, doing nothing.

946
01:10:11,336 --> 01:10:13,213
Thought you'd get it.

947
01:10:13,922 --> 01:10:17,509
So I'm telling you.
Only you, not them.

948
01:10:17,842 --> 01:10:22,514
They'd be upset that we could've
spent more time together.

949
01:10:24,140 --> 01:10:26,976
Hanging out there felt good.

950
01:10:27,018 --> 01:10:30,355
- You know how...
- See, that's just... That's it!

951
01:10:31,272 --> 01:10:34,192
This is exactly what I meant. This.

952
01:10:34,234 --> 01:10:38,321
That crap I have to listen to.
What's true, what's not...

953
01:10:38,363 --> 01:10:40,573
I knew it, I'm not dumb.

954
01:10:44,035 --> 01:10:45,829
I didn't forget that.

955
01:10:45,870 --> 01:10:49,124
Your endless stories,
and words, words, words,

956
01:10:49,165 --> 01:10:52,836
to confuse us, and fuck us over!

957
01:10:53,169 --> 01:10:56,172
You get away with it,
and I'm lost!

958
01:10:57,215 --> 01:11:01,386
- You're sick, Antoine.
- I'm sick now? No, you're sick!

959
01:11:01,803 --> 01:11:05,640
I know your little story!
The airport, the café...

960
01:11:05,682 --> 01:11:09,269
And what else? All those details...

961
01:11:09,310 --> 01:11:14,774
A dude cooking fries, your clothes
soaking up the smell of grease...

962
01:11:14,816 --> 01:11:19,070
And you were alone, all alone
in the airport, weren't you?

963
01:11:19,654 --> 01:11:21,865
You could hear a pin drop.

964
01:11:22,365 --> 01:11:25,994
So, you're there.
Reading your paper?

965
01:11:26,036 --> 01:11:28,121
I bet you are!

966
01:11:28,163 --> 01:11:30,123
Or some money magazine,

967
01:11:30,165 --> 01:11:33,043
with the shiny paper
and the big red letters...

968
01:11:40,383 --> 01:11:44,387
And I don't know either
why you came, Louis.

969
01:11:44,846 --> 01:11:47,474
No one knows. No one understands.

970
01:11:47,515 --> 01:11:50,226
And you hate that,
'cause if we knew...

971
01:11:50,268 --> 01:11:52,687
Oh, it'd be easy!

972
01:11:52,729 --> 01:11:56,900
You'd have taken off already,
or wouldn't have come!

973
01:11:58,193 --> 01:11:59,986
But you think that matters?

974
01:12:00,028 --> 01:12:05,033
Think airports, cafés,
magazines matter to me?

975
01:12:05,367 --> 01:12:09,162
You're wrong, buddy!
It doesn't matter at all!

976
01:12:09,537 --> 01:12:11,664
It doesn't matter anymore!

977
01:12:13,375 --> 01:12:16,878
That's not what you thought
at the airport.

978
01:12:16,920 --> 01:12:19,464
Or you weren't going to tell me.

979
01:12:19,881 --> 01:12:23,677
You're saying that to fill
the void between us.

980
01:12:24,302 --> 01:12:27,931
Bam, I'm here!
So you're making shit up.

981
01:12:27,972 --> 01:12:31,267
You made all that up
to talk to me?

982
01:12:31,309 --> 01:12:34,312
So I'd feel special.

983
01:12:34,813 --> 01:12:36,272
Special?

984
01:12:36,940 --> 01:12:40,777
To know you could've
spent more time with us?

985
01:12:42,529 --> 01:12:45,490
You didn't think that.
We're strangers.

986
01:12:45,532 --> 01:12:47,701
Strangers share nothing.

987
01:12:47,742 --> 01:12:51,287
We're strangers, Louis.
Haven't we always been?

988
01:12:51,996 --> 01:12:54,916
You thought "I'll take that angle,

989
01:12:54,958 --> 01:12:57,168
so I can handle him."

990
01:12:58,169 --> 01:12:59,254
You thought...

991
01:12:59,295 --> 01:13:04,009
"I've studied, lived, written...
I can handle him."

992
01:13:04,050 --> 01:13:06,803
Funny. People say that of me...

993
01:13:06,845 --> 01:13:09,264
He's hard to handle.

994
01:13:09,556 --> 01:13:12,017
"Handle Antoine with kid gloves!"

995
01:13:12,058 --> 01:13:15,562
Like an animal in a cage.

996
01:13:15,603 --> 01:13:18,106
That you pet. And kill.

997
01:13:18,148 --> 01:13:20,859
That's what you did
at the airport, Louis.

998
01:13:21,818 --> 01:13:26,197
You thought you had a technique
to grab me.

999
01:13:27,407 --> 01:13:29,617
But I'm not in the mood.

1000
01:13:29,868 --> 01:13:32,537
I'm not interested.

1001
01:13:33,079 --> 01:13:36,791
What are you doing here?
I don't wanna know!

1002
01:13:37,542 --> 01:13:38,918
I don't care.

1003
01:13:39,419 --> 01:13:42,255
You're here, you're not.
That's your problem.

1004
01:13:42,297 --> 01:13:46,843
You're home. You come,
you go, you stay. Fine.

1005
01:13:46,885 --> 01:13:49,596
Not everything's so great
in your small life.

1006
01:13:49,637 --> 01:13:52,182
- `Cause it is small.
- Antoine, slow down.

1007
01:13:52,223 --> 01:13:57,270
You were at the airport café,
thinking about sweet nothing!

1008
01:13:57,312 --> 01:14:00,065
The coffee's giving you the runs,

1009
01:14:00,106 --> 01:14:02,317
you're thinking about no one!

1010
01:14:02,359 --> 01:14:05,320
You're there,
living your fucking life,

1011
01:14:05,362 --> 01:14:08,239
so get the fuck over it already!

1012
01:15:20,478 --> 01:15:21,855
- Antoine?
- No.

1013
01:15:22,355 --> 01:15:26,067
I don't wanna be here.
And listen to you. Or talk.

1014
01:15:28,028 --> 01:15:29,612
I'm scared. You happy?

1015
01:15:34,075 --> 01:15:37,120
You guys always have to
tell me everything.

1016
01:15:37,162 --> 01:15:38,496
And I have to listen

1017
01:15:38,997 --> 01:15:41,499
I hate listening. I hate talking.

1018
01:15:45,795 --> 01:15:48,882
We think silent people
are good listeners.

1019
01:15:49,716 --> 01:15:52,844
But I shut up so people
leave me alone.

1020
01:15:53,845 --> 01:15:55,347
Do you get that?

1021
01:15:58,850 --> 01:16:00,101
Do you?

1022
01:16:01,644 --> 01:16:03,146
I do.

1023
01:16:04,647 --> 01:16:05,899
Amazing.

1024
01:16:13,782 --> 01:16:14,908
By the way...

1025
01:16:15,658 --> 01:16:17,827
Pierre died last week. Cancer.

1026
01:16:18,578 --> 01:16:19,704
Pierre?

1027
01:16:19,746 --> 01:16:21,581
Jolicoeur.

1028
01:16:23,333 --> 01:16:25,377
Pierre Jolicoeur, your Pierre.

1029
01:16:34,135 --> 01:16:37,222
I better help with dessert
or they'll gimme hell.

1030
01:17:07,085 --> 01:17:08,837
Antoine, is that you?

1031
01:17:11,256 --> 01:17:12,966
Where is everyone?

1032
01:17:13,466 --> 01:17:15,969
- What?
- Where are the others?

1033
01:17:16,011 --> 01:17:17,303
I dunno.

1034
01:17:17,345 --> 01:17:18,680
Here.

1035
01:17:18,722 --> 01:17:20,515
Hold this while I...

1036
01:17:23,643 --> 01:17:26,396
<i>I think I heard someone come in.</i>

1037
01:17:26,730 --> 01:17:30,734
<i>Shouldn't I go get everyone?
I think it was Antoine.</i>

1038
01:17:30,775 --> 01:17:33,028
<i>They'll come when they're ready.</i>

1039
01:17:33,069 --> 01:17:34,612
<i>Help me with this.</i>

1040
01:17:44,289 --> 01:17:45,582
I don't get it.

1041
01:17:45,623 --> 01:17:46,666
What?

1042
01:17:49,085 --> 01:17:50,503
Think you're alone?

1043
01:17:54,716 --> 01:17:56,509
You're handsome when you smile.

1044
01:18:00,096 --> 01:18:05,143
You think we're alone?
Think Mom gets any of this?

1045
01:18:08,730 --> 01:18:11,441
No one gets it.
Never did, never will.

1046
01:18:12,400 --> 01:18:14,652
That's the beauty of it, right?

1047
01:18:15,362 --> 01:18:17,947
<i>I think Antoine and Louis
had a fight.</i>

1048
01:18:17,989 --> 01:18:19,574
Get outta here.

1049
01:18:22,827 --> 01:18:23,661
Antoine!

1050
01:18:25,163 --> 01:18:26,915
Yeah, coming!

1051
01:18:29,292 --> 01:18:30,585
There was no drama...

1052
01:18:30,627 --> 01:18:33,672
I was young, I can't remember,
but there was no drama...

1053
01:18:33,713 --> 01:18:36,424
tragic stuff, or betrayals,

1054
01:18:37,008 --> 01:18:38,343
or murders.

1055
01:18:39,636 --> 01:18:41,680
Shit like that...
So he'd avoid us.

1056
01:18:41,721 --> 01:18:42,972
He doesn't care.

1057
01:18:44,974 --> 01:18:47,519
<i>He doesn't feel the need for "us".</i>

1058
01:18:48,019 --> 01:18:49,396
<i>He wants to be far.</i>

1059
01:18:49,437 --> 01:18:52,107
<i>He's almost farther
sitting on our couch.</i>

1060
01:18:52,941 --> 01:18:54,067
He's the sad one.

1061
01:18:54,109 --> 01:18:57,487
He missed all those years,
never saw you grow.

1062
01:18:58,363 --> 01:18:59,864
And life went on,

1063
01:19:00,365 --> 01:19:03,284
<i>as it does today, invariably.</i>

1064
01:19:03,326 --> 01:19:04,828
Just like in books.

1065
01:19:20,593 --> 01:19:23,847
<i>You're unhappy, but only
'cause it's convenient.</i>

1066
01:19:23,888 --> 01:19:27,267
<i>- So choose to be happy.
- Easy to say.</i>

1067
01:19:27,308 --> 01:19:29,185
Anyway, it's almost over.

1068
01:19:29,227 --> 01:19:31,396
Really? Why?

1069
01:20:14,731 --> 01:20:15,690
So...

1070
01:20:15,732 --> 01:20:17,400
Yep!

1071
01:20:17,692 --> 01:20:21,071
Appetizers, mains,
finger food... Nope.

1072
01:20:21,696 --> 01:20:24,908
But desserts?
I'm just unbeatable.

1073
01:20:31,790 --> 01:20:33,375
I...

1074
01:20:34,250 --> 01:20:36,336
I've got something to tell you.

1075
01:20:36,753 --> 01:20:38,254
Things, actually.

1076
01:20:43,343 --> 01:20:44,928
I'll come back.

1077
01:20:45,428 --> 01:20:47,013
And more often.

1078
01:20:49,307 --> 01:20:51,101
And write.

1079
01:20:52,352 --> 01:20:53,937
More often.

1080
01:20:54,312 --> 01:20:56,731
Not just two
or three words.

1081
01:20:58,316 --> 01:20:59,943
Because...

1082
01:21:02,737 --> 01:21:04,489
I regret it all.

1083
01:21:06,533 --> 01:21:09,786
The time we've wasted.
The time I've wasted.

1084
01:21:14,457 --> 01:21:18,044
Suzanne, if you want to visit,
you're welcome.

1085
01:21:18,086 --> 01:21:21,631
For a weekend, or longer,
as you wish. We'll set it...

1086
01:21:26,511 --> 01:21:28,471
And Antoine...

1087
01:21:28,763 --> 01:21:30,640
If we had dinner,

1088
01:21:30,682 --> 01:21:33,518
we could continue
the conversation we began,

1089
01:21:33,560 --> 01:21:35,311
calmly.

1090
01:21:35,854 --> 01:21:37,522
When I'm back. Or you come.

1091
01:21:37,564 --> 01:21:39,566
I can't. Too much work.

1092
01:21:39,607 --> 01:21:41,359
A weekend?

1093
01:21:43,236 --> 01:21:44,696
Just a weekend.

1094
01:21:45,113 --> 01:21:46,364
Weekends are just as...

1095
01:21:46,406 --> 01:21:49,159
Everyone can survive
a weekend, Antoine.

1096
01:21:51,661 --> 01:21:54,247
You can. You have the right to.

1097
01:21:57,709 --> 01:22:01,129
- You love the city.
- I love the city, now?

1098
01:22:05,592 --> 01:22:07,344
You always did.

1099
01:22:43,213 --> 01:22:45,131
Truth is, I have to go.

1100
01:22:50,095 --> 01:22:52,722
- What are you doing?
- What's wrong?

1101
01:22:52,764 --> 01:22:56,309
When all is well,
Antoine messes things up!

1102
01:22:56,351 --> 01:22:58,436
Or are you tidying up?

1103
01:22:58,770 --> 01:23:00,605
Don't hold your breath.

1104
01:23:02,899 --> 01:23:04,567
What's wrong with you two?

1105
01:23:04,609 --> 01:23:08,655
Are you drunk? Or high?
You guys got high?

1106
01:23:09,155 --> 01:23:10,532
He's used to it.

1107
01:23:13,952 --> 01:23:16,621
I'll drive you. No more cabs.

1108
01:23:17,038 --> 01:23:18,331
- What?
- Here.

1109
01:23:18,373 --> 01:23:20,792
Already, now?

1110
01:23:20,834 --> 01:23:22,836
Didn't he say that?

1111
01:23:22,877 --> 01:23:24,796
No.

1112
01:23:24,838 --> 01:23:26,589
Louis, you're
staying tonight?

1113
01:23:26,631 --> 01:23:28,883
My bad! In the car, didn't you say

1114
01:23:28,925 --> 01:23:31,594
you had a meeting tonight?

1115
01:23:31,636 --> 01:23:33,304
Tonight, right?

1116
01:23:33,346 --> 01:23:34,848
Are you insane, Antoine?

1117
01:23:34,889 --> 01:23:36,891
I'm not insane, I listen.

1118
01:23:36,933 --> 01:23:40,478
He has to go,
so I kindly offer my help.

1119
01:23:40,520 --> 01:23:43,481
Airport's 40 minutes
from your mom's, right?

1120
01:23:43,523 --> 01:23:45,358
That's right, honey.

1121
01:23:45,400 --> 01:23:47,944
I'll grab the kids on my way.

1122
01:23:47,986 --> 01:23:51,406
Excuse me, how long to
the airport? 40 minutes?

1123
01:23:51,448 --> 01:23:52,741
When d'you last go?

1124
01:23:52,782 --> 01:23:54,451
You've never been!

1125
01:23:54,492 --> 01:23:57,871
I go all the time, idiot,
Julien lives there!

1126
01:23:57,912 --> 01:24:00,081
So? What's the difference?

1127
01:24:00,123 --> 01:24:02,542
He's not taking another cab!

1128
01:24:02,584 --> 01:24:04,919
That isn't the point, Antoine!

1129
01:24:05,337 --> 01:24:07,005
It is not the point!

1130
01:24:12,385 --> 01:24:14,220
Louis...

1131
01:24:14,262 --> 01:24:15,513
You're going?

1132
01:24:15,889 --> 01:24:19,100
I can drive you,
tonight, or tomorrow.

1133
01:24:19,142 --> 01:24:20,226
You sleep over,

1134
01:24:20,268 --> 01:24:22,020
we have breakfast.

1135
01:24:23,855 --> 01:24:25,231
What's that meeting?

1136
01:24:25,273 --> 01:24:27,275
Yes, what's that meeting?

1137
01:24:27,317 --> 01:24:29,569
Is it that important?

1138
01:24:31,988 --> 01:24:33,490
It can't wait?

1139
01:24:35,158 --> 01:24:38,286
On a Sunday, I mean...

1140
01:24:40,246 --> 01:24:42,248
You said it was crucial.

1141
01:24:42,290 --> 01:24:43,792
Shut up!

1142
01:24:51,466 --> 01:24:53,385
What's the problem, here?

1143
01:24:54,469 --> 01:24:56,638
We were doing fine!

1144
01:24:57,514 --> 01:24:59,391
In a moment, pow!

1145
01:25:00,433 --> 01:25:02,268
Why, Louis?

1146
01:25:03,687 --> 01:25:04,688
Why?

1147
01:25:13,571 --> 01:25:15,323
Because.

1148
01:25:17,242 --> 01:25:18,660
I have a meeting.

1149
01:25:19,786 --> 01:25:21,496
Thank you. Let's go.

1150
01:25:21,538 --> 01:25:24,416
What the fuck, Antoine!
Don't touch him!

1151
01:25:37,929 --> 01:25:39,180
What's wrong?

1152
01:25:39,848 --> 01:25:42,600
- Antoine, I'm fine!
- Just helping...

1153
01:25:42,642 --> 01:25:46,730
What the hell's going on!
This is pure madness!

1154
01:25:46,771 --> 01:25:49,399
No! He'll miss his plane.

1155
01:25:49,441 --> 01:25:54,279
- We can at least kiss goodbye.
- Now! Kiss kiss, chop chop!

1156
01:25:54,320 --> 01:25:56,698
Only two seconds ago we were...

1157
01:25:56,740 --> 01:25:58,450
eating nicely,

1158
01:25:58,491 --> 01:26:00,994
speaking happily, sharing a moment

1159
01:26:01,036 --> 01:26:02,954
and you just act up,

1160
01:26:02,996 --> 01:26:05,623
breaking, spoiling
every bit of it!

1161
01:26:05,665 --> 01:26:07,500
I'm warning you,

1162
01:26:07,542 --> 01:26:08,918
I won't forget this.

1163
01:26:09,419 --> 01:26:11,921
Your brother was trying...
I don't get it.

1164
01:26:11,963 --> 01:26:13,882
- It's okay, Mom.
- Kissy, kissy, come on!

1165
01:26:13,923 --> 01:26:15,300
- Antoine...
- Shut up!

1166
01:26:15,342 --> 01:26:18,970
Jesus! I'll drive him!
Louis, let me take you!

1167
01:26:19,012 --> 01:26:20,472
Suzanne, stop!

1168
01:26:20,513 --> 01:26:22,265
I'm driving him!

1169
01:26:22,307 --> 01:26:26,019
- We can't drive like a...
- Like what? Say it!

1170
01:26:27,312 --> 01:26:30,398
I'm driving him! The end!
I'll be back in an hour.

1171
01:26:30,440 --> 01:26:32,400
- You're so despicable!
- Me?

1172
01:26:32,442 --> 01:26:35,570
You don't hear yourself!
See yourself!

1173
01:26:35,612 --> 01:26:38,615
How you rush him!
How you talk to me!

1174
01:26:38,656 --> 01:26:40,200
And your wife!

1175
01:26:41,868 --> 01:26:43,370
You...

1176
01:26:43,411 --> 01:26:45,538
you little piece of shit.

1177
01:26:46,706 --> 01:26:50,126
- Come on, defend me!
- Of course she will!

1178
01:26:50,168 --> 01:26:51,795
Suzanne?

1179
01:26:53,004 --> 01:26:54,589
I don't get it.

1180
01:26:56,132 --> 01:26:57,717
So I'll come visit?

1181
01:27:05,141 --> 01:27:06,601
Let's go, Louis.

1182
01:27:07,143 --> 01:27:08,353
Louis!

1183
01:27:11,815 --> 01:27:12,816
See you soon.

1184
01:27:13,566 --> 01:27:16,194
Let him go, you fucking psycho!

1185
01:27:16,236 --> 01:27:17,529
What did I do?

1186
01:27:17,987 --> 01:27:19,489
What you do is,

1187
01:27:19,531 --> 01:27:23,910
you ruin our fucking lives
and our day with Louis

1188
01:27:23,952 --> 01:27:25,787
with your brutality!

1189
01:27:25,829 --> 01:27:28,039
Brutality? My... Me?

1190
01:27:28,456 --> 01:27:30,000
Yes, you!

1191
01:27:30,041 --> 01:27:32,627
- Antoine.
- Stop, I'm fine!

1192
01:27:32,669 --> 01:27:35,380
Calm down.
It's okay, just...

1193
01:27:35,422 --> 01:27:38,216
Calm us... Calm yourself.

1194
01:27:38,925 --> 01:27:40,635
Don't be so brutal.

1195
01:27:40,677 --> 01:27:43,888
Who's brutal? I'm trying to help!

1196
01:27:43,930 --> 01:27:46,141
You weren't brutal,
it's a misunder...

1197
01:27:46,182 --> 01:27:49,394
- You! Goodness incarnate...
- Brutal and stupid!

1198
01:27:52,355 --> 01:27:56,609
You understand shit!
You know shit!

1199
01:27:56,651 --> 01:27:58,528
So shut your mouth, bitch!

1200
01:27:58,570 --> 01:28:02,365
Don't ever talk to
your sister like that!

1201
01:28:02,407 --> 01:28:05,702
Fine! Y'know what?
You figure it out.

1202
01:28:05,744 --> 01:28:08,413
I screwed up, as usual.

1203
01:28:08,455 --> 01:28:11,124
So go for it, Louis.
Go for it!

1204
01:28:11,166 --> 01:28:12,417
Go!

1205
01:28:15,545 --> 01:28:19,966
He said "I must go."
Those very words!

1206
01:28:20,008 --> 01:28:23,762
Is it my fucking fault again?

1207
01:28:23,803 --> 01:28:25,138
Is it?

1208
01:28:26,556 --> 01:28:30,852
You guys think I'm an idiot!
And I've had it!

1209
01:28:31,227 --> 01:28:34,314
There was nothing bad
in what I did!

1210
01:28:34,564 --> 01:28:35,565
Let's go.

1211
01:28:38,610 --> 01:28:43,365
It's not fair! You treat me
like I'm a circus freak!

1212
01:28:44,741 --> 01:28:46,284
It's not fair.

1213
01:28:46,326 --> 01:28:51,498
You've no right! You can't always
win! You can't do that to me!

1214
01:28:54,042 --> 01:28:55,543
Don't cry, Antoine...

1215
01:28:55,585 --> 01:28:56,670
I'll kill you!

1216
01:28:56,711 --> 01:28:58,004
Antoine, no!

1217
01:29:03,718 --> 01:29:05,595
Don't touch him, Louis.

1218
01:29:07,472 --> 01:29:09,265
Come. Don't.

1219
01:29:09,599 --> 01:29:12,018
Stop it. Get away from him.

1220
01:29:16,439 --> 01:29:17,732
Antoine, it's over.

1221
01:29:19,192 --> 01:29:20,318
Come.

1222
01:29:26,366 --> 01:29:27,367
It's over.

1223
01:29:56,396 --> 01:29:58,982
We'll be better prepared
next time.

1224
01:33:41,746 --> 01:33:46,001
in loving memory of François Barbeau

1225
01:38:36,499 --> 01:38:42,922
Subtitling consultant:
Robert Gray, <i>Kinograph</i>

